            "value": "%3Cp%3EDavid%20was%20in%20a%20mess.%20He%20had%20done%20a%20foolish%20thing%20when%20he%20tempted%20the%20Lord%20by%20counting%20his%20fighting%20men.%20God%20gave%20him%20three%20choices%20of%20judgment%2C%20and%20they%20all%20sounded%20bad!%20David%20wisely%20chose%20the%20option%20that%20involved%20God's%20mercy%2C%20for%20he%20said%2C%20%22But%20let%20us%20fall%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Lord%2C%20for%20his%20mercy%20is%20great.%20Do%20not%20let%20me%20fall%20into%20human%20hands%22%20(2%20Samuel%2024%3A14).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20man%20at%20the%20gate%20Beautiful%20looked%20at%20thousands%20of%20people%20every%20day%20as%20he%20begged%20for%20financial%20mercies.%20Peter%20addressed%20the%20man%2C%20saying%2C%20%22Look%20at%20us!%22%20(Acts%203%3A4).%20Peter%20wanted%20the%20lame%20man%20to%20look%20to%20the%20Lord%20for%20His%20mercy.%20The%20power%20of%20the%20name%20of%20Jesus%20healed%20the%20man%2C%20who%20joyfully%20jumped%20up%2C%20%22walking%2C%20leaping%2C%20and%20praising%20God%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(v.%208).%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWe%20may%20look%20to%20many%20men%20and%20various%20sources%20to%20help%20us%20through%20our%20problems%2C%20but%20eventually%20we%20must%20go%20to%20%22the%20source%20of%20every%20mercy%20and%20the%20God%20who%20comforts%20us%22%20(2%20Corinthians%201%3A3).%20Are%20you%20in%20trouble%3F%20Don't%20take%20your%20eyes%20off%20God%20your%20Father%2C%20for%20%22his%20mercy%20endureth%20for%20ever%22%20(Psalm%20118%3A1%20KJV).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
